# Development Rules for Gemini - 3Dworks

## Code Generation Standards

### Framework Rules
- ALWAYS use Next.js 16 App Router (never Pages Router)
- Default to Server Components; only use 'use client' when needed for:
  - useState, useEffect, other React hooks
  - Event handlers (onClick, onChange)
  - Browser APIs (window, document)
  - Third-party libraries requiring client-side
- TypeScript strict mode - no any types

### Styling Rules
- ONLY use Tailwind utility classes (core utilities, no arbitrary values unless necessary)
- shadcn/ui components for all UI elements
- Mobile-first: write sm: md: lg: xl: breakpoints
- Light mode first, dark mode via dark: prefix (automatically switches on system preference)
- Light mode: bg-white bg-slate-50 text-slate-900 text-slate-600
- Dark mode: dark:bg-[#050505] dark:bg-[#0a0a0f] dark:text-white
- Modern aesthetic with minimal rounding (rounded-sm, rounded-md preferred over rounded-lg)
- Glassmorphism (theme-aware):
  - Light: backdrop-blur-md bg-black/5 border border-black/10 shadow-sm
  - Dark: dark:backdrop-blur-md dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-white/10
- Consistent spacing: p-4, p-6, p-8, p-12 pattern
- NO custom CSS files, NO styled-components, NO emotion

### Color System
**Light Mode (default):**
- Backgrounds: bg-white bg-slate-50 bg-gray-50
- Text: text-slate-900 text-slate-600 text-slate-500
- Borders: border-slate-200 border-slate-300
- Surface cards: bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm
- Overlays: bg-black/5 bg-slate-500/10

**Dark Mode (dark: prefix):**
- Backgrounds: dark:bg-[#050505] dark:bg-[#0a0a0f] dark:bg-zinc-950
- Text: dark:text-white dark:text-slate-200 dark:text-slate-400
- Borders: dark:border-white/10 dark:border-slate-800
- Surface cards: dark:bg-white/5 dark:backdrop-blur-md dark:border-white/10
- Overlays: dark:bg-white/5 dark:bg-blue-500/10

**Brand Colors (both modes):**
- Primary: text-cyan-500 bg-cyan-500 border-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-600
- Secondary: text-purple-500 bg-purple-500 border-purple-500
- Accent: text-cyan-400 bg-cyan-400
- Success: text-emerald-500 bg-emerald-500

### Component Patterns
```typescript
// Server Component (default)
interface Props {
  title: string;
  items: Item[];
}

export default function Section({ title, items }: Props) {
  return <div>...</div>;
}

// Client Component (when needed)
'use client';

import { useState } from 'react';

export function InteractiveGallery() {
  const [filter, setFilter] = useState('all');
  return <div>...</div>;
}
```

### Animation Rules
- Framer Motion for complex animations
- Use motion.div, motion.section, etc.
- Simple transitions: transition-all duration-300 ease-out
- Respect reduced motion: motion-reduce:transition-none
- Scroll animations: IntersectionObserver or Framer's viewport props
- 3D transforms: transform-gpu for performance

### File Structure
```
/app
  /page.tsx (homepage)
  /layout.tsx
  /globals.css
  /api
/components
  /ui (shadcn)
  /sections
    /Hero.tsx
    /Portfolio.tsx
    /Services.tsx
  /shared
/lib
  /utils.ts
  /db.ts
/public
  /images
  /models
```

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (Hero.tsx, PortfolioCard.tsx)
- Utils/functions: camelCase (cn, formatDate)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- CSS classes: kebab-case (only in rare custom CSS)

### Database Patterns
- Use Server Actions for data mutations
- Async/await for all DB operations
- Proper error handling with try/catch
- Type-safe queries with TypeScript

### What NOT to Do
- ❌ No localStorage/sessionStorage in initial render (causes hydration issues)
- ❌ No inline styles (use Tailwind)
- ❌ No default exports except page.tsx files
- ❌ No console.logs in production code
- ❌ No unoptimized images (always use next/image)
- ❌ No client components when server components work
- ❌ No excessive border-radius (keep it sharp and modern)

### Quality Checklist
Before completing any component:
- [ ] TypeScript types defined
- [ ] Responsive on all breakpoints
- [ ] Accessible (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)
- [ ] Loading/error states handled
- [ ] Images optimized
- [ ] Animations smooth (60fps)
- [ ] Glassmorphism effects applied consistently

### SEO Requirements
- Metadata in layout.tsx and page.tsx
- Alt text on all images
- Semantic HTML (header, main, section, article)
- Structured data where applicable
